FBIS4-24277 "drafr124_d_94014" FBIS-AFR-94-124 Daily Report 28 Jun 1994 SOUTHERN AFRICA Mozambique British Military Advisers To Remain Until Elections British Military Advisers To Remain Until Elections MB2806090694 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 0800 GMT 28 Jun 94 MB2806090694 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network Portuguese BFN [Text] The MOZAMBIQUE INFORMATION AGENCY cites a British Embassy spokesman in Maputo as saying the British officers advising in the training of the joint Mozambican army will remain in the country until the October elections are held. The officers, whose mission was scheduled to end on 1 July, are assisting in the training of 15 infantry battalions of the Mozambique Defense Armed Forces.
